  schema:name "From Seed to Seedling" ;
  schema:description "Explanation of germination as a developmental transition: seed dormancy as adaptive bet-hedging, dormancy-breaking signals, the germination process from imbibition to seedling establishment, and the energy costs of growth" ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-04-02" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-04-02" ;
  emsenn:Addresses "Why seeds wait before germinating; what breaks dormancy in nature; the mechanics of radicle emergence and shoot growth; why germination speed varies among species" ;
